Advertisement call. Description based on 522 calls recorded from seven males ( Table 3 ). The call consists of single, pulsed notes given at a rate of 145–196 per minute (
Fig. 6g
). Note duration varies from 62–126 ms. Rise time varies from 26–94% of note duration. Notes are formed by 6–12 complete pulses emitted at a rate of 75–125 per second. The dominant frequency coincides with the fundamental harmonic at 586–1383 Hz. Notes usually have a modest frequency upsweep throughout their duration, varying from 141–750 Hz.
